        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Keep ambiguous delivery attempts recoverable",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Keeps outbound delivery entries in ambiguous post-send states pending when adapter reconciliation is unavailable.\n- Preserves the existing no-blind-replay behavior while leaving the entry retryable for later reconciliation/backoff.\n- Avoids consuming retry budget when no reconciliation-capable adapter ran, so ambiguous entries do not age into terminal failure before a later adapter can reconcile them.\n- Updates startup recovery, reconnect-drain, and outbound queue integration coverage plus Discord troubleshooting guidance for #87544.\n\n## Scope\n\nThis is a narrow mitigation for #87544 and intentionally does not close the full issue. The broader transcript-to-provider delivery ledger, Discord reconciliation semantics, and UI/API surfacing still need maintainer design.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/outbound/deliver.queue-integration.test.ts src/infra/outbound/delivery-queue.recovery.test.ts src/infra/outbound/delivery-queue.reconnect-drain.test.ts`\n  - 3 files passed, 43 tests passed.\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/infra/outbound/delivery-queue-storage.ts src/infra/outbound/delivery-queue-recovery.ts src/infra/outbound/deliver.queue-integration.test.ts src/infra/outbound/delivery-queue.recovery.test.ts src/infra/outbound/delivery-queue.reconnect-drain.test.ts docs/channels/troubleshooting.md`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: ambiguous outbound delivery entries whose platform send may have started must not be blindly replayed, and must remain pending/recoverable without consuming retry budget when adapter reconciliation is unavailable.\n\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw source checkout on macOS with Node v22.22.3, rebased onto `openclaw/openclaw@c5d34c8376f8aa32744786cae0473c60e39ef444`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: ran a one-off `node --import tsx --input-type=module` terminal proof that invoked the real `enqueueDelivery`, `markDeliveryPlatformOutcomeUnknown`, `recoverPendingDeliveries`, `loadPendingDeliveries`, and SQLite state reader against a temporary OpenClaw state directory. The proof queued an `unknown_after_send` outbound entry, ran recovery with no reconciliation-capable adapter, and failed if `deliver` was called, the entry did not remain pending, or retry budget was consumed.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\ninfo: Found 1 pending delivery entries — starting recovery\nwarn: Delivery entry <redacted-queue-id> delivery state is unknown_after_send; refusing blind replay without adapter reconciliation\nwarn: Retry failed for delivery <redacted-queue-id>: delivery state is unknown_after_send; refusing blind replay without adapter reconciliation\ninfo: Delivery recovery complete: 0 recovered, 1 failed, 0 skipped (max retries), 0 deferred (backoff)\nproof summary: {\"recovered\":0,\"failed\":1,\"skippedMaxRetries\":0,\"deferredBackoff\":0}\ndeliver call count: 0\npending entries: 1\nqueue row: {\"status\":\"pending\",\"retry_count\":0,\"recovery_state\":\"unknown_after_send\",\"last_error\":\"delivery state is unknown_after_send; refusing blind replay without adapter reconciliation\"}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: recovery refused blind replay, did not call the delivery function, kept exactly one pending queue entry, and persisted `status: \"pending\"`, `retry_count: 0`, and `recovery_state: \"unknown_after_send\"`.\n\nWhat was not tested: no live Discord gateway/channel send was performed in this pass. The broader transcript-to-provider delivery ledger, Discord reconciliation semantics, and Control UI/API delivery-state surface remain open under #87544.\n",
        "branch": "codex/discord-delivery-reconciliation",
